All these initiatives cost big money even as sales tax revenues dry up.
In a recent address, Garcetti said he expected a 30% to 40% drop in the city’s hotel occupancy tax and significant decreases in sales tax revenue.
The mayor has moved $20 million from city reserves into an emergency COVID-19 response fund, but he said the city needs help.
Prior to coronavirus, Fresno’s economy was in one of the best shapes it had been in a long time.
People are losing jobs and sales tax, a big source of city revenue, is being significantly impacted.